overview: The user initiated the project by providing a Statement of Work for a
  sleep questionnaire application and sought assistance in implementing a
  database, an admin dashboard, and authentication. The model began by
  thoroughly evaluating the existing codebase, identifying key missing
  functionalities such as response storage, data retrieval, and an
  administrative interface. After clarifying user preferences for a simple
  password-based authentication and specific demographic data fields, a
  comprehensive plan was developed. This plan encompassed updating data models,
  creating API endpoints for data persistence and retrieval (including CSV
  export), and building a basic admin dashboard with login capabilities. During
  implementation, the authentication system was refined to leverage Next.js
  middleware for a more streamlined and efficient approach to route protection.
  The model then guided the user through the database setup process, including
  environment variable configuration and Prisma migrations, and concluded by
  demonstrating the core functionality through a browser-based test, ensuring
  all requirements were met.
